# VisaTrack

**AI-powered visa and document tracking for stress-free applications.**

VisaTrack helps anyone navigating a visa application stay organized. Tell it your destination country and purpose — it automatically generates your required document checklist using AI, lets you track progress, upload files, and get personalized guidance through an AI advisor.

Built for the [H0 — Hack the Zero Stack with Vercel v0 & AWS Databases](https://h01.devpost.com) hackathon.

---

## Live Demo

- **Frontend:** https://application-tracker-jet.vercel.app
- **Backend API:** https://application-tracker-production-3af2.up.railway.app

---

## The Problem

Visa applications are overwhelming. Dozens of documents, strict deadlines, country-specific requirements — and no clear way to know where you stand. People miss appointments, forget requirements, and get rejected over small paperwork mistakes.

VisaTrack fixes that by combining AI-generated checklists with a clean, simple tracker so applicants always know exactly what they need and where they are in the process.

---

## Features

**Core**
- AI-generated document checklist based on destination country and visa purpose
- Per-document status tracking (Required → In Progress → Completed)
- File upload and management for each document
- Progress bar showing overall application completion

**AI Features**
- Visa Guide — AI-generated step-by-step guide tailored to your country and visa type
- Chat with Advisor — conversational AI that answers questions about your specific application (Pro)

**Community**
- Share tips and experiences with other applicants

**Pro Tier**
- Unlimited applications (free tier: 1 application)
- Chat with Advisor access

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Vercel |
| Backend | Django, Django REST Framework, Python |
| Database | Amazon Aurora PostgreSQL (Serverless v2) |
| Auth | JWT via SimpleJWT |
| AI | Google Gemini 2.5 Flash |
| Hosting | Vercel (frontend) · Railway (backend) |
| Cloud | AWS (Aurora PostgreSQL, IAM Authentication) |

---

## AWS Database

VisaTrack uses **Amazon Aurora PostgreSQL (Compatible with PostgreSQL 17.7)** deployed as a serverless v2 cluster in `eu-north-1`.

- **Cluster:** `visatrack-db`
- **Engine:** Aurora PostgreSQL 17.7
- **Type:** Serverless v2 (0–4 ACUs, auto-scaling)
- **Auth:** IAM Database Authentication via boto3
- **Region:** eu-north-1 (Stockholm)

Aurora was chosen for its native PostgreSQL compatibility (works out of the box with Django ORM), serverless auto-scaling, and IAM-based authentication which eliminates static credentials.

---

## Architecture

```
┌─────────────────┐         ┌──────────────────────┐
│   React + TS    │  HTTPS  │   Django + DRF       │
│   Vercel        │────────▶│   Railway            │
└─────────────────┘         └──────────┬───────────┘
                                       │
                          ┌────────────┴────────────┐
                          │                         │
               ┌──────────▼──────────┐   ┌─────────▼────────┐
               │  Aurora PostgreSQL  │   │  Gemini 2.5 Flash │
               │  AWS (eu-north-1)  │   │  Google AI        │
               │  IAM Auth + boto3  │   └──────────────────┘
               └────────────────────┘
```

